<br>
Well, my monk had about 3 hours of level 48 PRE-patch when they changed the 40 hell levels. And then entered his 49 shortly after that patch.<br>
<br>
PRE-patch, Bloodgill Goblins were AMAZING XP at level 48. INSANE XP. Post patch they were so-so at 49. BUT at 50, because they hadn't messed with the 50s XP, the Bloodgills became insane again. It was actually disconcerting to see more XP movement per kill at 50 than at 49.<br>
<br>
In any event, I quickly entered 51, and forgot all about that change, UNTIL ...<br>
<br>
My Warrior hit his 30s. <br>
<br>
They tweaked the XP, yes. But HELL LEVELS ARE STILL THERE. Don't believe their hype. They're not as noticable. BUT, 30/35/40/45 DID take longer than they should have. XP lost at 31/36/41/46 WAS more than XP lost at the other levels, LIKE before (what can I say, I died a lot, heh. Thank god I have friends to help with rezzes).<br>
<br>
It's nowhere near as bad as it used to be. BUT, it's still there.<br>
<br>
My point? I have a feeling the 50s will still be HARD. Not nearly as hard as they used to be. But still hard.<br>
<br>
OR maybe the smoothing out of the 50s will actually retroactively affect the other levels, and this whole thing will finally get the kinks worked out.<br>
<br>
Heck, maybe VI will just magically DING us all 60 right before PoP comes out.<br>
<br>
That'd be neat.<br>
<br>
-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uyarlin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yarlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/25/02 8:34:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1134.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Say goodbye ter all hell levels</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
This does not change the amount of experience required to go from &quot;No experience in level 1&quot; to &quot;Full-bar in level 60.&quot; It's just about smoothing out the trip. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To those that don't understand, here is how it will work.<br>
<br>
Rather than bunching up the needed experience gains at levels 51 and 59, it will be evened out from 54 to 59.<br>
<br>
For those that don't understand here is how it will work.  Let's say it takes this much experience to get to 60 from 51:<br>
<br>
[Example only]<br>
51 - 100<br>
52 - 200<br>
53 - 300<br>
54 - 400<br>
55 - 500<br>
56 - 600<br>
57 - 700<br>
58 - 800<br>
59 - 900<br>
TOTAL EXP EXAMPLE = 4500<br>
<br>
Here is how it will work when it evens out:<br>
51 = 500<br>
52 = 500<br>
53 = 500<br>
54 = 500<br>
55 = 500<br>
56 = 500<br>
